(2) The bodies referred to in subsection (1) (a) above are—

(a) the council of a district, the Greater London Council, the council of a London borough, the Common Council of the City of London or the Council of the Isles of Scilly;

(b) a development corporation established by an order made, or having effect as if made, under the New Towns Act 1965;

(c) the Commission for the New Towns;

(d) the Development Board for rural Wales.

(2) A disposal falls within this sub-section if it is—

(a) a further conveyance of the freehold or an assignment of the lease; or

(b) the grant of lease or sub-lease for a term of more than 21 years otherwise than at a rack rent;
